        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:39PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 439 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Martinsville, or near Hazlehurst, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crystal Springs, Hazlehurst, Wesson, Beauregard, Gallman,
Martinsville, and Glancy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
